		"description": "<p>Sometimes the greater divine purpose requires a certain amount of subtlety and discretion. When these situations arise, you step in to resolve the issue. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You can spend a use of @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.s4iiatrup3e3virw]{Channel Divinity} to cast @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-spells.Item.0cdtrkihoe9jdon1]{Greater Invisibility} on yourself without using a spell slot.</li>\n<li>You may choose a second Principle of Devotion from the following options: @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.ofugczcz0tf3jbkl]{Devotional Integrity}, @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.yakt9uiyp07pc2c9]{Image of the Divine}, @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.d5k6klumbkvcagfm]{Secrecy}, and @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.eed5zt51yzu8zbet]{Silence}. You gain the restrictions and benefits of this second principle of devotion as normal. If you opt not to select one, you instead gain proficiency with a single finesse weapon of your choice.</li>\n<li>When you would gain a new Sign of Faith or Skill Trick, you can choose freely from either list and also from the herald class&rsquo;s @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.zj2p68ex28alzo9i]{Divine Lessons}.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with death saves.</li>\n</ul>",
